                        <td class="pagesubtitle">
                            1. What Are Cookies and How Do We Use Them?
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="pagecontent">
                            Infiniticlothing.com uses a browser feature known as a cookie, which assigns a unique
                            identification to your computer. The cookies are typically stored on your computer's
                            hard drive. Information collected from cookies is used by Infiniticlothing.com to
                            evaluate the effectiveness of our Website, analyze trends, and administer the Website.
                            The information collected from cookies allows us to determine such things as which
                            parts of our Website are most visited and difficulties our visitors may experience
                            in accessing our Website. With this knowledge, we can improve the quality of your
                            experience on our Website by recognizing and delivering more of the most desired
                            features and information, as well as by resolving access difficulties. In addition,
                            Infiniticlothing.com uses cookies to help keep track of items you put into your
                            shopping cart and to tell us whether you have visited Infiniticlothing.com in the
                            past. This allows visitors to the online store to maintain shopping carts between
                            visits. Infiniticlothing.com also uses cookies to help keeptrack of checkout information,
                            other than payment method information,while you remain on our site.<br />
                            Infiniticlothing.com also uses clear gifs (also known as Web beacons or Web bugs)
                            on the Website and in emails. A clear gif is a nearly invisible pixel-sized graphic
                            image on a Webpage oremail message. Clear gifs allow us to view the URL of the page
                            on which the clear gif appears and the time our Website or email in question is
                            viewed. Clear gifs in emails also help us confirm the receipt of,and response to,
                            our emails, and provide you with a more personalized experience when using our Website.
                            This information helps us determine the most desired features and information so
                            that we can provide those features and information to you.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
